00:22:12,211 --> 00:22:16,011
To make your lover blue

251
00:22:16,081 --> 00:22:19,107
Seven lonely days

252
00:22:19,184 --> 00:22:22,051
I cried and I cried for you

253
00:22:22,121 --> 00:22:25,648
Oh, my darling, you're crying

254
00:22:25,724 --> 00:22:28,522
Boohoohoohoo

255
00:22:43,909 --> 00:22:47,845
Your cheating heart

256
00:22:50,416 --> 00:22:54,614
Will make you weep

257
00:22:56,055 --> 00:22:59,855
You'll cry and cry

258
00:23:01,460 --> 00:23:05,726
And try to sleep

259
00:23:06,765 --> 00:23:12,294
But sleep won't come

260
00:23:12,371 --> 00:23:16,740
The whole night through

261
00:23:19,211 --> 00:23:22,544
Your cheating heart

262
00:23:24,316 --> 00:23:28,685
Will tell on you

263
00:23:30,155 --> 00:23:35,457
When tears come down

264
00:23:35,527 --> 00:23:40,464
Like falling rain

265
00:23:41,667 --> 00:23:45,068
You'll toss around

266
00:23:45,137 --> 00:23:46,798
Nice day.

267
00:23:46,872 --> 00:23:48,567
Great day.

268
00:23:48,640 --> 00:23:52,371
Do you want to top me
all the time? Just say,
"Yes, it's a nice day."

269
00:23:52,444 --> 00:23:55,038
Yes, it's a nice day.

270
00:23:57,850 --> 00:24:00,580
This water is cold.

271
00:24:00,652 --> 00:24:02,586
We used to come swimmin'
here up till November.

272
00:24:02,654 --> 00:24:05,680
I'm telling you, this water's
got ice cubes in it.

273
00:24:05,758 --> 00:24:09,956
A guy in my class says he saw an
8foot water moccasin in here...

274
00:24:10,028 --> 00:24:12,724
with his mouth open,
showing white.

275
00:24:12,798 --> 00:24:14,732
I ain't afraid of snakes.

276
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:17,564
Take a swim, big talk. Go ahead.

277
00:24:17,636 --> 00:24:20,628
I'll pay you. How much will
it take for you to jump in?

278
00:24:20,706 --> 00:24:23,470
What? I'm serious. How much?

279
00:24:23,542 --> 00:24:25,476
Three hundred.
You'd really do it?

280
00:24:25,544 --> 00:24:27,842
You got the cash? I love it!

281
00:24:27,913 --> 00:24:30,108
Man, I wish I had $300.

282
00:24:30,182 --> 00:24:33,481
You don't have it?
I ain't jumping in for nothin'.

283
00:24:33,552 --> 00:24:35,486
I'll save you.

284
00:24:42,728 --> 00:24:45,663
You want to have other
nice days like today?

285
00:24:45,731 --> 00:24:47,198
Sure.

286
00:24:47,266 --> 00:24:50,633
I mean lots of them. Sure.

287
00:24:50,702 --> 00:24:52,670
No, I mean lots of them.

288
00:24:54,273 --> 00:24:56,901
Good times all the
time, Sunday to Sunday.

289
00:24:59,044 --> 00:25:00,477
What?

290
00:25:01,747 --> 00:25:03,339
Charlie?

291
00:25:03,415 --> 00:25:05,383
Wanna get married?

292
00:25:06,885 --> 00:25:08,318
I dare you!

293
00:25:10,389 --> 00:25:11,822
Yes!

294
00:25:18,864 --> 00:25:21,992
You telling me yes? Yes!

295
00:25:29,775 --> 00:25:32,437
Beautiful. Doesn't
she look beautiful?

296
00:25:34,446 --> 00:25:36,437
Are you ready?

297
00:25:36,515 --> 00:25:37,948
We're ready.

298
00:25:42,321 --> 00:25:43,754
Byebye.

299
00:25:47,426 --> 00:25:50,862
If you find yourself
wondering what to do in
the dark, give me a call.

300
00:25:50,929 --> 00:25:53,523
I think I can manage.
I'll see you at work.

301
00:25:53,599 --> 00:25:55,032
On Monday morning.

302
00:25:55,100 --> 00:25:56,567
Byebye, Mama.

303
00:25:56,635 --> 00:25:59,263
I love you, sugar.
You take care of yourself.

304
00:25:59,338 --> 00:26:03,365
You look so pretty today. Bye.

305
00:26:15,287 --> 00:26:18,814
What the hell you been
doing in there? Come here.

306
00:26:30,435 --> 00:26:34,337
It's kind of scary,
isn't it? What do you mean?

307
00:26:34,406 --> 00:26:37,864
You go out and buy a new dress...

308
00:26:37,943 --> 00:26:40,605
stand in front of a
preacher, say a few words...

309
00:26:40,679 --> 00:26:43,273
suddenly everything's changed.

310
00:26:45,751 --> 00:26:49,812
I just want it to work out,
Charlie. I want everything
to be right.

311
00:26:51,723 --> 00:26:53,156
Well, come here.

312
00:26:57,095 --> 00:26:59,154
Wait.

313
00:26:59,231 --> 00:27:01,222
This is my wedding night.

314
00:27:01,300 --> 00:27:03,461
I want the words.

315
00:27:04,102 --> 00:27:06,593
Say the words.

316
00:27:09,508 --> 00:27:11,442
I love you.

317
00:27:13,045 --> 00:27:15,104
Say it again.
I love you, goddamn it!

318
00:27:15,180 --> 00:27:17,239
That's so nice.

319
00:27:17,316 --> 00:27:19,784
I want this to work out, too.

320
00:27:19,851 --> 00:27:22,251
I'm sure as hell gonna try.

321
00:27:22,321 --> 00:27:24,551
Yeah? Yeah.

322
00:27:53,852 --> 00:27:56,446
Here. You look like you
need this more than me.

323
00:27:56,521 --> 00:27:59,422
God bless you, mister.

324
00:27:59,491 --> 00:28:01,721
Big night, huh?

325
00:28:01,793 --> 00:28:03,226
Real big.

326
00:28:05,831 --> 00:28:09,198
Tell me. How was the
honeymoon? Nice?

327
00:28:09,267 --> 00:28:11,792
Hell, yeah. It was wonderful.

328
00:28:11,870 --> 00:28:16,000
Two days at a cutrate
motel. It was great.

329
00:28:16,074 --> 00:28:19,737
Real uptown stuff.
Pasty didn't like it?

330
00:28:19,811 --> 00:28:23,008
Patsy didn't say a word.
She wouldn't. I didn't like it.

331
00:28:23,081 --> 00:28:26,448
I didn't like it. Jesus,
you're in a mood.

332
00:28:26,518 --> 00:28:28,918
I've got $12 to my name.

333
00:28:28,987 --> 00:28:32,320
Twelve dollars until payday.
The money ain't so bad here.

334
00:28:32,391 --> 00:28:33,983
Or so good.

335
00:28:34,059 --> 00:28:35,788
What do you want?

336
00:28:35,861 --> 00:28:39,422
Want to be like that old
fart, Lawrence?
Wear a suit, run the place?

337
00:28:39,498 --> 00:28:42,399
Hell, no.

338
00:28:42,467 --> 00:28:47,097
I'd just like somethin'
different maybe. Do something
a little better.

339
00:28:47,172 --> 00:28:49,936
I'd like to get my
own place maybe.

340
00:28:50,008 --> 00:28:52,533
I don't care,
I ain't gonna do it.

341
00:28:52,611 --> 00:28:56,809
The idea of you asking me to
go on television and lie.

342
00:28:56,882 --> 00:28:59,442
I am not asking you to lie.

343
00:28:59,518 --> 00:29:03,386
All you've got to do is say,
"Mr. Godfrey, I'm Hilda Hensley.

344
00:29:03,455 --> 00:29:06,481
I brought my friend Patsy
Cline. I'm her talent scout."

345
00:29:06,558 --> 00:29:08,526
That's not a lie.
You are my friend.

346
00:29:08,593 --> 00:29:12,154
I ain't gonna do it,
so stop flapping your jaws at me.

347
00:29:12,230 --> 00:29:16,291
That man from the show told
you that talent scouts
can't be a relative.

348
00:29:18,103 --> 00:29:21,971
Is that why you give me
that housecoat of yours
with the puff sleeves?

349
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:24,941
I give you that housecoat
'cause you said you liked it.

350
00:29:25,010 --> 00:29:27,604
Well, I won't lie on television.

351
00:29:27,679 --> 00:29:30,409
Goddamn it! I'm not
asking you to lie.

352
00:29:30,482 --> 00:29:32,882
Just don't spill your
guts is all I'm askin'.

353
00:29:32,951 --> 00:29:35,385
Stop that dirty talk now.

354
00:29:37,422 --> 00:29:41,358
Mama, think of what it could mean
to sing on national television.

355
00:29:42,260 --> 00:29:44,626
All you gotta do is just say...

356
00:29:44,696 --> 00:29:47,426
"Mr. Godfrey, I'm Hilda Hensley.

357
00:29:47,499 --> 00:29:50,627
I've brought my friend Patsy
Cline. I'm her talent scout."

358
00:29:52,204 --> 00:29:54,172
Come on, Mama.

359
00:29:54,239 --> 00:29:57,208
Do I have to get on my
knees and beg you? I will.

360
00:29:57,275 --> 00:30:02,110
Please! Help me to be a
singer, have my house with
the yellow roses. Please!

361
00:30:02,180 --> 00:30:06,116
That house with the yellow roses!
I'm sick of hearing about it.

362
00:30:06,184 --> 00:30:08,152
What does Charlie
say about all this?

363
00:30:08,220 --> 00:30:10,916
He thinks it's a terrific idea.

364
00:30:10,989 --> 00:30:13,082
Well, I ain't gonna do it.

365
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:17,924
The idea of me on television.

366
00:30:29,508 --> 00:30:30,941
Thirty seconds.

367
00:30:33,478 --> 00:30:35,412
They're from
Winchester, Virginia.

368
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:37,380
Patsy, I can't do it.

369
00:30:37,449 --> 00:30:39,974
You can, too. Don't be
an old chicken.

370
00:30:40,051 --> 00:30:42,747
You look beautiful.
A little color in your cheeks.

371
00:30:42,821 --> 00:30:46,382
Mrs. Hensley? You're on.
Follow me. Just say what
we practiced.

372
00:30:46,458 --> 00:30:48,892
Say what we practiced and
smile. You look real pretty.

373
00:30:49,961 --> 00:30:52,930
You're better looking
than her, Woodhouse.

374
00:30:52,998 --> 00:30:56,195
Get her off of there.
Let's see Patsy.

375
00:30:56,268 --> 00:31:00,068
Marla Kleinman. Remember, folks.

376
00:31:00,138 --> 00:31:03,107
Your applause is on
the applause meter.

377
00:31:07,579 --> 00:31:09,206
Get lost! Stop it.

378
00:31:09,281 --> 00:31:11,078
Hello and welcome.

379
00:31:11,149 --> 00:31:13,276
There's your mama!

380
00:31:13,351 --> 00:31:17,253
That is a pretty dress.
What color is that exactly?

381
00:31:17,322 --> 00:31:20,155
Mr. Godfrey, I'm Hilda Hensley.

382
00:31:20,225 --> 00:31:23,126
And I brought my
friend Patsy Cline.

383
00:31:23,195 --> 00:31:25,561
And I'm her talent scout. Good.

384
00:31:25,630 --> 00:31:28,121
Miss Cline, let's go.
Hurry please, around the back.

385
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:30,430
Where are you from?
Winchester, Virginia.

386
00:31:30,502 --> 00:31:35,132
That's lovely country. So,
what's Patsy's talent?

387
00:31:35,207 --> 00:31:36,640
She sings.

388
00:31:36,708 --> 00:31:38,676
Does she sing better than I do?

389
00:31:38,743 --> 00:31:41,177
Oh. Well, she's...

390
00:31:41,246 --> 00:31:43,578
She's wonderful.
She made a record.

391
00:31:43,648 --> 00:31:46,674
Why don't we bring her out?
Ladies and gentlemen...

392
00:31:46,751 --> 00:31:49,345
let's welcome Patsy Cline.

393
00:31:51,656 --> 00:31:54,284
Come on, Patsy! Come on, baby!

394
00:31:55,694 --> 00:32:00,154
I go out walkin' after midnight

395
00:32:00,232 --> 00:32:04,931
Out in the moonlight
just like we used to do

396
00:32:05,003 --> 00:32:08,905
I'm always walkin' after midnight

397
00:32:08,974 --> 00:32:11,772
Searchin' for you

398
00:32:11,843 --> 00:32:14,175
She looks great, don't she?

399
00:32:14,246 --> 00:32:18,580
I walk for miles
along the highway

400
00:32:18,650 --> 00:32:23,314
Well, that's just my way
of sayin' I love you

401
00:32:23,388 --> 00:32:27,415
I'm always walkin' after midnight

402
00:32:27,492 --> 00:32:30,859
Searchin' for you
That's beautiful.

403
00:32:32,397 --> 00:32:37,767
I stopped to see a weepin'
willow cryin' on his pillow

404
00:32:37,836 --> 00:32:41,738
Maybe he's cryin' for me

405
00:32:41,806 --> 00:32:44,297
You lucky boy.
She could make it big.

406
00:32:44,376 --> 00:32:47,072
Night winds whisper to me

407
00:32:47,145 --> 00:32:51,343
I'm lonesome as I can be

408
00:32:51,416 --> 00:32:55,648
She's singing good.
I go out walkin' after midnight

409
00:32:55,720 --> 00:33:00,680
Out in the moonlight
just hopin' you may be

410
00:33:00,759 --> 00:33:04,855
Somewhere out walkin'
after midnight

411
00:33:04,929 --> 00:33:09,923
Searchin' for me

412
00:33:12,337 --> 00:33:14,100
Patsy Cline!

413
00:33:15,607 --> 00:33:17,905
This Virginia gal can sing.

414
00:33:17,976 --> 00:33:20,774
Let us hear from you
through the applause meter.

415
00:33:20,845 --> 00:33:23,939
Watch the meter. Come on,
people, clap louder.

416
00:33:24,015 --> 00:33:25,346
Go, go!

417
00:33:27,218 --> 00:33:29,743
Patsy Cline is the winner!

418
00:33:30,655 --> 00:33:32,520
She won!

419
00:33:59,651 --> 00:34:01,209
Bull's eye!

420
00:34:02,253 --> 00:34:06,280
A little draggy to me that
time. Patsy, that's all right.

421
00:34:06,358 --> 00:34:09,794
This is gonna make us all a
whole lot of money, little girl.

422
00:34:09,861 --> 00:34:14,855
Listen, boys, you don't
mind if we try it one...
Come on. One more time.

423
00:34:14,933 --> 00:34:17,026
Thanks a lot, boys.

424
00:35:02,647 --> 00:35:04,581
I'm home, baby.

425
00:35:04,649 --> 00:35:06,947
Where've you been?
I stopped and had a drink.

426
00:35:07,018 --> 00:35:09,316
Yeah. Five or seven.

427
00:35:09,387 --> 00:35:12,618
I worked my hump off
making you baked chicken,
you come home this late.

428
00:35:12,690 --> 00:35:14,920
I'll eat it.

429
00:35:14,993 --> 00:35:20,829
You got a finger? Then put it
in a telephone and dial when
you'll be late.

430
00:35:20,899 --> 00:35:22,833
I said I'd eat the thing.

431
00:35:23,802 --> 00:35:27,431
Lady, I've got a message
for you. Screw your baked
chicken and screw you.

432
00:35:27,505 --> 00:35:30,941
Yeah? That's the last time I'm
gonna make you something nice.

433
00:35:31,009 --> 00:35:32,943
Oh, poor Patsy.

434
00:35:33,011 --> 00:35:35,536
You dumb son of a bitch!

435
00:35:35,613 --> 00:35:38,377
You want your dinner?
Why don't you eat it now?

436
00:35:38,450 --> 00:35:40,509
Gonna throw a plate?

437
00:35:46,090 --> 00:35:48,320
You wanna start on
the living room?

438
00:35:50,395 --> 00:35:52,659
Charlie, look what you've done!

439
00:35:52,730 --> 00:35:54,721
Goddamn it!

440
00:36:06,544 --> 00:36:09,342
Sip it slow and the
world stays sweet.

441
00:36:10,381 --> 00:36:12,941
My daddy used to say
that same thing.

442
00:36:15,720 --> 00:36:18,154
Do my back, baby,
would you please?

443
00:36:20,959 --> 00:36:23,154
He was something, my old man.

444
00:36:23,228 --> 00:36:27,289
He used to eat cold navy
bean sandwiches for
breakfast every morning.

445
00:36:29,868 --> 00:36:31,859
I hope he rots in hell.

446
00:36:31,936 --> 00:36:33,927
What do you mean?

447
00:36:34,005 --> 00:36:35,438
He's crazy.

448
00:36:36,474 --> 00:36:38,874
He tried some stuff with me once.

449
00:36:38,943 --> 00:36:41,434
You telling me he tried
to mess with you?

450
00:36:42,680 --> 00:36:46,081
I don't want to talk about
that now. How come you
never told me about that?

451
00:36:46,150 --> 00:36:48,710
How come you never say
anything about your family?

452
00:36:48,786 --> 00:36:50,879
Not when I'm in such a good mood.

453
00:36:50,955 --> 00:36:52,889
Hello? Patsy Cline?

454
00:36:52,957 --> 00:36:55,949
That's me. What? Who is it?

455
00:36:56,027 --> 00:36:58,461
Is it Woodhouse? Hush up.

456
00:36:58,530 --> 00:37:01,693
I'm sorry. I didn't hear
you. Tell him he made me
late for dinner.

457
00:37:01,766 --> 00:37:04,860
For the love of God,
put a lid on it. Yes, ma'am.

458
00:37:04,936 --> 00:37:07,564
I'm sorry, my husband's
a little nuts.

459
00:37:07,639 --> 00:37:10,267
This is Decca Records. What?

460
00:37:13,845 --> 00:37:18,805
That's Decca Records.
" Walkin' after Midnight"
jumped to number 16!

461
00:37:18,883 --> 00:37:21,852
I am on the son of
a bitchin' charts!

462
00:37:22,754 --> 00:37:25,188
Goddamn it, baby!

463
00:37:25,256 --> 00:37:27,315
Let's go spend some money.

464
00:37:37,468 --> 00:37:39,402
I got a letter from Washington.

465
00:37:41,005 --> 00:37:45,135
Probably from Eisenhower,
wanting to know why I
didn't vote for him.

466
00:37:47,345 --> 00:37:49,279
Shit! I've been drafted.

467
00:37:51,849 --> 00:37:54,545
What? They want me to
show up next week.

468
00:37:54,619 --> 00:37:56,917
I can't be drafted.
I'm in the National Guard.

469
00:37:58,556 --> 00:38:01,616
You said they never miss
you at those meetings.

470
00:38:01,693 --> 00:38:05,129
Well, I ain't goin',
I'll tell you that much.

471
00:38:05,196 --> 00:38:07,687
I'll shoot my toe off.

472
00:38:07,765 --> 00:38:11,428
I'll tell 'em I'm a
homo. I ain't goin'!

473
00:38:12,870 --> 00:38:16,271
I love you. Take care
of yourself.

474
00:38:16,341 --> 00:38:17,774
Bye, baby.

475
00:38:19,811 --> 00:38:24,908
Well, now, it ain't
the end of the world.

476
00:38:24,983 --> 00:38:30,114
Fort Bragg's not exactly
a million miles away.

477
00:38:30,188 --> 00:38:32,122
You've got that tour coming up.

478
00:38:32,190 --> 00:38:37,093
Shit! Why don't you tell me every
cloud's got a silver linin'?

479
00:38:37,161 --> 00:38:40,255
Why don't you move
in with me, honey?

480
00:38:40,331 --> 00:38:43,095
No sense in paying
rent on your place.

481
00:38:51,676 --> 00:38:54,406
Well, good mornin'.

482
00:38:54,479 --> 00:38:56,379
Says who?

483
00:38:56,447 --> 00:38:59,974
For heaven's sake.
Sit up and take some nourishment.

484
00:39:00,051 --> 00:39:02,576
Charlie'll have his first
leave in three weeks...

485
00:39:02,654 --> 00:39:06,488
and you walk around with your
lower lip draggin' the floor.

486
00:39:06,557 --> 00:39:10,550
Big bawlin' baby.
I oughta fix you a sugar tit.

487
00:39:12,463 --> 00:39:15,830
You're still not too big
for me to smack your jaws
for you. You know that?

488
00:39:15,900 --> 00:39:19,267
You make that sign again,
I'll leave the print of
my hand across your face.

489
00:39:19,337 --> 00:39:21,567
I'll make your teeth rattle.

490
00:39:24,909 --> 00:39:28,003
For those of you who've
got to get to work,
it's 8:30 in the morning.

491
00:39:28,079 --> 00:39:31,515
Let's continue listening
to everybody's favorites.

492
00:39:33,918 --> 00:39:35,510
I got a check today.

493
00:39:40,725 --> 00:39:45,890
Why don't you go out and
spend some money?
It'll make you feel better.

494
00:39:45,963 --> 00:39:47,863
Says who?

495
00:39:47,932 --> 00:39:51,459
You're just too mean
to live lately.

496
