01:04:56,739 --> 01:04:59,731
I cannot believe this!

743
01:05:03,179 --> 01:05:08,549
Honey, your mama's life is not
workin' out. Trust me. It's not.

744
01:05:09,986 --> 01:05:14,923
I'm goin' to Nashville tomorrow.
See if I can do something.

745
01:05:40,083 --> 01:05:42,017
Aren't you Patsy Cline?

746
01:05:42,085 --> 01:05:43,313
Yeah.

747
01:05:43,386 --> 01:05:44,819
I'm Randy Hughes.

748
01:05:44,887 --> 01:05:48,050
I was just coming to
see you. Is that right?

749
01:05:48,124 --> 01:05:50,456
You wrote me a letter
about a year ago.

750
01:05:50,526 --> 01:05:53,791
But I had a baby and haven't
been doin' much singing.

751
01:05:53,863 --> 01:05:56,161
You don't have to sell me.

752
01:05:56,232 --> 01:05:59,690
I think you're maybe the best
country singer in the world.

753
01:06:01,237 --> 01:06:03,296
Come in here.
Let's you and I talk.

754
01:06:03,373 --> 01:06:07,935
I always did like a man who knew
how to start a conversation good.

755
01:06:08,011 --> 01:06:11,708
I swear, I can make us
both a lot of money.

756
01:06:11,781 --> 01:06:15,148
You won't be sorry.
You know why not? Why?

757
01:06:15,218 --> 01:06:18,381
Because when the song is
right and I feel it...

758
01:06:18,454 --> 01:06:23,187
I can tell from looking
at people's faces that
I've reached inside them.

759
01:06:23,259 --> 01:06:25,489
You got any idea what
that feels like?

760
01:06:25,561 --> 01:06:27,461
You want to be Kitty Wells?

761
01:06:27,530 --> 01:06:30,328
Hell no! I want to
be Hank Williams.

762
01:06:30,400 --> 01:06:34,359
All right. Sit down,
listen to me.

763
01:06:35,738 --> 01:06:38,298
I got a story to tell you.

764
01:06:39,709 --> 01:06:43,008
I heard you sing one night
in a dump in Virginia.

765
01:06:43,079 --> 01:06:45,912
Twelve tables,
watereddown drinks...

766
01:06:45,982 --> 01:06:48,314
dance floor the size
of that coffee table.

767
01:06:48,384 --> 01:06:50,648
You were good.

768
01:06:50,720 --> 01:06:55,054
The crowd liked ya.
Ate up that yodelin'
and growlin' stuff.

769
01:06:55,124 --> 01:07:00,528
Then you let go on "Walkin'
the Floor Over You."

770
01:07:00,596 --> 01:07:04,430
But you did it slow
like a ballad.

771
01:07:05,568 --> 01:07:10,596
I'm tellin' you, the hair on
the back of my neck stood up.

772
01:07:11,574 --> 01:07:14,634
There I was in this
dive in Virginia...

773
01:07:14,711 --> 01:07:18,272
and I was listening to
something real special.

774
01:07:18,348 --> 01:07:19,781
Yeah.

775
01:07:19,849 --> 01:07:24,013
You get my drift?
I'll make it simple.

776
01:07:25,088 --> 01:07:30,549
You got a voice that was
made to sing love songs.

777
01:07:32,061 --> 01:07:36,293
If I work with you,
we take advantage of that fact.

778
01:07:38,868 --> 01:07:42,702
I don't wanna talk about
it anymore. I got starving
kids waiting in the car.

779
01:07:42,772 --> 01:07:44,763
It's too late. It's all set up.

780
01:07:44,841 --> 01:07:49,471
I don't give a damn!
I don't want four big male
singers drowning me out.

781
01:07:49,545 --> 01:07:52,036
They're booked and
will be there at 2:00.

782
01:07:52,115 --> 01:07:54,481
If they're there,
I'm not showing up.

783
01:07:54,550 --> 01:07:58,145
Musicians are booked.
Owen Bradley's gonna be
there. I'm gonna be there.

784
01:07:58,221 --> 01:08:00,917
You can show up or not.
Just suit your damn self.

785
01:08:00,990 --> 01:08:02,423
I will.

786
01:08:02,492 --> 01:08:04,119
2:00.

787
01:08:04,193 --> 01:08:06,753
Grab hold of Randy, Madrine.

788
01:08:07,764 --> 01:08:11,461
They got four singers backing
me up today. Big ones.

789
01:08:11,534 --> 01:08:15,163
They're just gonna drown
me out. Hell's bells!

790
01:08:15,238 --> 01:08:18,002
Let's have the next bit.

791
01:08:18,074 --> 01:08:20,008
One, two.

792
01:08:28,484 --> 01:08:31,180
Hello. Did you tell
'em what I said?

793
01:08:31,254 --> 01:08:34,052
Mr. Bradley's the
producer, darling.

794
01:08:35,124 --> 01:08:37,456
Hello, Patsy. Hi, Mr. Bradley.

795
01:08:37,527 --> 01:08:39,961
What's the frown for?
You've been worryin' again.

796
01:08:40,029 --> 01:08:42,497
Don't frown. You'll make
yourself old before your time.

797
01:08:42,565 --> 01:08:45,796
I wanted to talk to
you... Listen to me.
Everything's all right.

798
01:08:45,868 --> 01:08:48,234
The song's a good one.
The arrangement's a good one.

799
01:08:48,304 --> 01:08:51,034
The backup singers are
good. Even the glazed
doughnuts are good.

800
01:08:51,107 --> 01:08:55,043
Everything's good today,
so relax and be happy and sing!

801
01:08:56,946 --> 01:08:58,971
Just make sure they hear me.

802
01:08:59,048 --> 01:09:01,209
Sing!

803
01:09:01,284 --> 01:09:03,548
Take seven coming up.

804
01:09:18,034 --> 01:09:21,629
I can see you all recognize
that song. That's great.

805
01:09:21,704 --> 01:09:27,074
We happen to have the little girl
backstage that made that famous.

806
01:09:27,143 --> 01:09:32,581
We're proud of her at the Grand
Old Opry. Miss Patsy Cline!

807
01:09:39,121 --> 01:09:43,353
I fall

808
01:09:43,426 --> 01:09:46,554
To pieces

809
01:09:49,031 --> 01:09:53,730
Each time I see you again

810
01:09:56,572 --> 01:10:00,702
I fall

811
01:10:00,776 --> 01:10:03,108
To pieces

812
01:10:06,015 --> 01:10:11,510
How can I be just your friend

813
01:10:13,422 --> 01:10:16,914
You want me to act

814
01:10:16,993 --> 01:10:21,259
Like we've never kissed

815
01:10:21,330 --> 01:10:25,562
You want me to forget

816
01:10:25,635 --> 01:10:29,628
Pretend we've never met

817
01:10:29,705 --> 01:10:32,139
And I've tried

818
01:10:32,208 --> 01:10:34,904
And I've tried

819
01:10:34,977 --> 01:10:38,572
But I haven't yet

820
01:10:38,648 --> 01:10:40,616
You walk by

821
01:10:40,683 --> 01:10:45,677
And I fall to pieces

822
01:11:04,640 --> 01:11:10,010
I like everything you
sing. You just open your
mouth and I fall down.

823
01:11:10,079 --> 01:11:12,707
But when you sing
those slow ones...

824
01:11:12,782 --> 01:11:15,546
I just love it.

825
01:11:15,618 --> 01:11:19,054
Randy told me it's number
nine on the pop charts.

826
01:11:19,121 --> 01:11:22,056
I'm a crossover.
Money, money, money!

827
01:11:23,859 --> 01:11:27,124
I wanna buy Mama a
pure silk dress.

828
01:11:27,196 --> 01:11:30,324
Give Sylvia that graduation
party she never had.

829
01:11:31,567 --> 01:11:33,728
I want to spend
some of that money.

830
01:11:33,803 --> 01:11:37,330
I'll tell you what.
I'll help you do it.

831
01:11:40,509 --> 01:11:43,706
I'm home. Had to crawl
part way, but I made it.

832
01:11:44,880 --> 01:11:46,848
That's pretty.

833
01:11:46,916 --> 01:11:49,350
Bake that all by your Ionesome?

834
01:11:49,418 --> 01:11:50,851
I sure did.

835
01:11:53,723 --> 01:11:56,351
How come you didn't bake
me a cake for my birthday?

836
01:11:57,426 --> 01:11:59,917
Goddamn it! That's not funny.

837
01:11:59,996 --> 01:12:02,328
Been working on that all day.

838
01:12:04,333 --> 01:12:07,200
Didn't this pie turn out nice?

839
01:12:07,269 --> 01:12:10,830
Did it with tapioca
just like Mama does.

840
01:12:10,906 --> 01:12:14,239
I can't wait to see her and
John and Sylvie tomorrow.

841
01:12:20,149 --> 01:12:23,676
Why don't you go easy on that
drinkin' tomorrow at the party?

842
01:12:24,754 --> 01:12:27,018
Why don't you kiss my furry butt?

843
01:12:28,090 --> 01:12:30,024
You think I wouldn't?

844
01:12:35,631 --> 01:12:39,590
Come on, Charlie.
I'm cooking chicken.

845
01:12:40,670 --> 01:12:43,867
Stop it. Everything's gonna burn.

846
01:12:43,939 --> 01:12:47,204
Where are the kids
at? They're upstairs
in their bedroom.

847
01:12:47,276 --> 01:12:50,404
Come on. Oh, Lord!

848
01:12:50,479 --> 01:12:52,743
On the linoleum floor...

849
01:12:52,815 --> 01:12:55,181
with my dress up around my ears?

850
01:12:55,251 --> 01:12:56,684
Charlie!

851
01:12:58,554 --> 01:13:01,148
Red hots. Get your red hots here.

852
01:13:03,125 --> 01:13:07,528
Here's a taker for you.
Come on now. Like New York City.

853
01:13:14,904 --> 01:13:16,337
Come on!

854
01:13:16,405 --> 01:13:19,306
Hey, everybody. Listen a minute.

855
01:13:19,375 --> 01:13:23,436
We have a high school
graduate in our family
for the very first time.

856
01:13:23,512 --> 01:13:26,003
Charlie and I finally
got enough money...

857
01:13:26,082 --> 01:13:28,107
Finally!

858
01:13:28,184 --> 01:13:30,118
To give her a party
and buy her a present.

859
01:13:30,186 --> 01:13:33,553
Here it is. Happy graduation.
It's a new toothbrush.

860
01:13:39,328 --> 01:13:42,263
Don't Sylvia looks sweet today?

861
01:13:42,331 --> 01:13:44,458
I love her new hairdo.

862
01:13:44,533 --> 01:13:46,865
I'm gonna put him
down. He's so crabby.

863
01:13:46,936 --> 01:13:49,928
Good night, honey.
Give Grandma a kiss.

864
01:13:51,273 --> 01:13:54,208
Here, sweetheart. Put him down.

865
01:13:54,276 --> 01:13:56,301
Give Mama a kiss.

866
01:13:57,847 --> 01:14:02,580
Oh. It just kills me
I don't see him more.

867
01:14:02,651 --> 01:14:04,881
I know it. I wrote that book.

868
01:14:06,622 --> 01:14:08,681
How's things with
you and Charlie?

869
01:14:10,226 --> 01:14:12,786
Up and down?

870
01:14:12,862 --> 01:14:15,330
There's lots of up and down.

871
01:14:15,397 --> 01:14:16,830
Oh, Patsy!

872
01:14:20,536 --> 01:14:21,969
Geez, Mama.

873
01:14:23,539 --> 01:14:28,670
You know Charlie. He drinks a
little, but I knew that when
I married him.

874
01:14:28,744 --> 01:14:31,679
Other than that,
things are silky smooth.

875
01:14:32,882 --> 01:14:34,873
When he drinks,
he's got a temper.

876
01:14:34,950 --> 01:14:37,248
Does he hit you?

877
01:14:37,319 --> 01:14:40,846
Just that one time.

878
01:14:41,924 --> 01:14:46,293
They say if a man hits you once,
there's always another time.

879
01:14:46,362 --> 01:14:50,230
Sis, you have some money?
We want some more beer.

880
01:14:50,299 --> 01:14:52,995
I wanna go with you.

881
01:14:53,068 --> 01:14:55,628
See you in a minute.

882
01:15:01,477 --> 01:15:04,674
You don't remember
Barbara Simmons?

883
01:15:04,747 --> 01:15:07,341
You had crush on her all
through the fifth grade.

884
01:15:07,416 --> 01:15:09,646
You're a damn liar.

885
01:15:09,718 --> 01:15:12,551
I don't know why, though,
with that frizzy brown hair.

886
01:15:12,621 --> 01:15:15,385
What about you and
old Homer Atkinson?

887
01:15:15,457 --> 01:15:18,187
I never liked Homer Atkinson!

888
01:15:18,260 --> 01:15:20,854
You loved Homer
Atkinson. I did not!

889
01:15:20,930 --> 01:15:23,728
You called him every
night and hang up...

890
01:15:23,799 --> 01:15:25,824
when he answered.

891
01:15:26,435 --> 01:15:28,062
Look out!

892
01:15:37,813 --> 01:15:40,077
Somebody help me!

893
01:16:27,529 --> 01:16:29,793
The babies.

894
01:16:29,865 --> 01:16:31,799
Where are the babies?

895
01:16:33,369 --> 01:16:35,564
Patsy, they're fine.

896
01:16:36,772 --> 01:16:38,967
John's all right, too.

897
01:16:40,042 --> 01:16:42,806
You had us scared a little bit.

898
01:16:47,216 --> 01:16:50,811
Tell me. Are the babies alive?

899
01:16:50,886 --> 01:16:55,585
Honey, little Randy and
Julie weren't with you.

900
01:16:56,659 --> 01:16:59,355
John was with you, and he's okay.

901
01:17:23,852 --> 01:17:25,843
The kids are sleeping.

902
01:17:34,129 --> 01:17:36,063
Good night.

903
01:17:55,250 --> 01:17:58,219
Relax. Just a moment.

904
01:18:00,622 --> 01:18:02,055
Forceps, please.

905
01:18:09,531 --> 01:18:10,998
Very good.

906
01:18:11,867 --> 01:18:13,698
That's fine.

907
01:18:13,769 --> 01:18:15,964
That's very good. Fine, fine.

908
01:18:16,038 --> 01:18:18,233
Just as we expected.
It's healing nicely.

909
01:18:21,443 --> 01:18:23,741
Is it that bad?
It's not that bad...

910
01:18:23,812 --> 01:18:25,746
I wanna look.

911
01:18:25,814 --> 01:18:31,309
When the stitches come out,
the scars will heal very quickly.

912
01:18:35,190 --> 01:18:38,216
This is what I got to deal with?

913
01:18:42,131 --> 01:18:45,328
You cut your suit
to fit your cloth.

914
01:18:45,401 --> 01:18:47,926
Later you can have plastic
surgery if you want.

915
01:18:50,506 --> 01:18:54,909
Hell yes, I want plastic
surgery. I want all I can get.

916
01:18:54,977 --> 01:18:58,071
Maybe you can make me
look like Grace Kelly.

917
01:19:11,427 --> 01:19:13,952
Cut it. Cut it, please.

918
01:19:14,029 --> 01:19:15,826
Mr. Bradley...

919
01:19:15,898 --> 01:19:19,891
I don't care how many times
you play that, I can't sing
this man's songs.

920
01:19:19,968 --> 01:19:21,936
I don't know how
to sing like that.

921
01:19:22,004 --> 01:19:25,405
Nobody wants you to.
You can take it away from him.

922
01:19:25,474 --> 01:19:29,604
Yeah. The hell with the demo.
Steal the son of a bitch.

923
01:19:30,846 --> 01:19:35,510
I don't understand why
everything has to be so
hard. How am I to do this?

924
01:19:35,584 --> 01:19:38,815
Just like you always
do. Your way.

925
01:19:38,887 --> 01:19:40,855
Let the song tell the story.

926
01:19:54,970 --> 01:19:57,438
Crazy

927
01:19:57,506 --> 01:20:01,499
I'm crazy for feelin'

928
01:20:01,577 --> 01:20:05,673
So lonely

929
01:20:07,149 --> 01:20:09,674
I'm crazy

930
01:20:11,153 --> 01:20:14,350
I think that's a good tempo.
Let's try it that way.

931
01:20:14,423 --> 01:20:16,391
Somebody bring me a beer.

932
01:20:16,458 --> 01:20:20,224
Will somebody bring the lady a
beer? Then we'll go for a take.

933
01:20:24,466 --> 01:20:26,263
Wonderin'

934
01:20:27,836 --> 01:20:33,706
What in the world did I do

935
01:20:36,745 --> 01:20:40,044
Oh, crazy

936
01:20:41,250 --> 01:20:45,209
For thinkin' that my love

937
01:20:45,287 --> 01:20:49,656
Could hold you

938
01:20:51,160 --> 01:20:55,062
I'm crazy for tryin'

939
01:20:55,130 --> 01:20:58,531
And crazy for cryin'

940
01:20:58,600 --> 01:21:04,061
And I'm crazy for lovin' you

941
01:21:47,716 --> 01:21:51,345
Oh, God, honey,
I hope you like it!

942
01:21:51,420 --> 01:21:53,581
It's so pretty.

943
01:21:53,655 --> 01:21:57,056
There. There it is.
See that white one
with the columns?

944
01:22:01,163 --> 01:22:03,324
Ain't it the truth?

945
01:22:04,666 --> 01:22:07,635
I fell in love with it
the minute I saw it.

946
01:22:09,137 --> 01:22:13,836
I'd like a pale,
pale blue carpet.

947
01:22:13,909 --> 01:22:18,539
Maybe a couple divans,
make a conversation area.

948
01:22:20,515 --> 01:22:21,777
Honey?

949
01:22:21,850 --> 01:22:24,751
Look at this.
We got a dishwasher.

950
01:22:26,455 --> 01:22:29,219
And an oven built
right into the wall.

951
01:22:29,291 --> 01:22:33,819
I want to check a roast,
all I have to do is open
the door like this.

952
01:22:33,895 --> 01:22:37,262
No more bending over.
The Queen of Sheba.

953
01:22:39,534 --> 01:22:43,368
Say you already bought
it? I paid down on it.

954
01:22:43,438 --> 01:22:45,872
Why didn't you tell me?

955
01:22:45,941 --> 01:22:48,273
I wanted to surprise you.

956
01:22:49,778 --> 01:22:51,370
You surprised me.

957
01:22:51,446 --> 01:22:56,008
The best thing we can do
with our money is put it
in bricks and mortar.

958
01:23:04,359 --> 01:23:07,226
That show went on
forever last night...

959
01:23:07,296 --> 01:23:10,788
and every minute of it
shows in my face today.

960
01:23:13,368 --> 01:23:18,067
I'm glad we saved "Crazy"
till the end. I think it
made a great encore.

961
01:23:19,775 --> 01:23:22,471
You love Charlie?

962
01:23:22,544 --> 01:23:23,841
What?

963
01:23:23,912 --> 01:23:25,504
You love him?

964
01:23:25,580 --> 01:23:30,040
Oh, come on. I couldn't
get along without Charlie.

965
01:23:30,118 --> 01:23:33,918
How's that song go?
" He may have been a headache,
but he never was a bore."

966
01:23:33,989 --> 01:23:36,514
That's Charlie.
Is that an answer?

967
01:23:38,894 --> 01:23:41,658
I think Charlie and I
deserve each other.

968
01:23:48,403 --> 01:23:50,963
Looks like Charlie might be
throwing you a little party.

969
01:23:51,039 --> 01:23:53,007
Sure does. Take care.

970
01:23:53,075 --> 01:23:56,067
I'll see you at the
session. All right.

971
01:23:56,144 --> 01:23:59,079
Try and get a little sleep
between now and Friday.

972
01:23:59,147 --> 01:24:01,411
Nightynight. Good night.

973
01:24:15,297 --> 01:24:18,425
Miss Patsy Cline! In person!

974
01:24:19,501 --> 01:24:22,766
My baby's home!
We're having a party.

975
01:24:22,838 --> 01:24:24,135
I see.

976
01:24:24,206 --> 01:24:29,906
Did you see my new car?
I bought an old clunker to
drive in the demo derby.

977
01:24:31,113 --> 01:24:32,705
How are you?

978
01:24:32,781 --> 01:24:37,480
You know most everybody.
This is Cindy.
John and Sarah from work.

979
01:24:38,820 --> 01:24:43,484
That there's...
I don't know who that is.

980
01:24:43,558 --> 01:24:47,961
This is Skip. He sold me that
car. I'm glad to meet you.

981
01:24:49,297 --> 01:24:51,925
Nice to meet you. Think I'll
get myself a beer.

982
01:24:52,000 --> 01:24:54,332
How'd it go tonight? All right.

983
01:24:54,403 --> 01:24:58,203
This your date, Otis?
Lucky man. Yeah, goddamn it.

984
01:24:58,273 --> 01:25:00,833
Help yourself to food in there.
Bought a bunch of Chinese.

985
01:25:00,909 --> 01:25:03,673
Let's us dance one.

986
01:25:03,745 --> 01:25:06,839
Come on. Don't be such
